assistant_prompt:
To ensure that services provided within a learning location are managed in a timely and effective way to meet customer needs, we can use a robust service-level agreement (SLA) that outlines specific performance metrics and expectations. The service team can then use this agreement as a basis for managing and monitoring the services provided within the learning location.

Here's an example of how this could be included in the start method of a service:
```
async start(locationId: string, serviceName: string, serviceDisplayName: string): Promise<void> {
  // Validate input parameters
  if (serviceName === null || serviceDisplayName === null || locationId === null) {
    throw new Error('Service name, service display name, or location ID must be provided.');
  }

  // Retrieve the service from the backend
  const service = await this.services.get(serviceName);
  if (!service) {
    throw new Error(`Service with name "${serviceName}" does not exist.`);
  }

  // Ensure the service is not already running
  if (await this.serviceManager.isServiceRunning(service)) {
    throw new Error(`Service with name "${serviceName}" is already running.`);
  }

  // Get the session store
  const sessionStore = this.sessionStoreFactory.createSessionStore(locationId);

  // Retrieve the current user's session
  const session = sessionStore.getCurrentSession(serviceName);

  // Ensure the session is not expired
  if (session?.expirationTime <= Date.now() / 1000) {
    throw new Error(`Session with name "${serviceName}" has expired.`);
  }

  // Start the service
  const serviceStartOptions = {
    sessionId: session.id,
    service: service.name,
  };
  await this.serviceManager.start(serviceStartOptions);

  // Log the start of the service
  console.log(`Service with name "${serviceName}" started in location ${locationId}.`);
}
```
In this example, we validate the input parameters, retrieve the service from the backend, ensure that the service is not already running, retrieve the current user's session, ensure that the session is not expired, and then start the service.

We also log the start of the service

